Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize has expressed concern over the rising number of COVID-19 cases in KwaZulu-Natal. #eNCA talks to Premier Sihle Zikalala about KZN's readiness for the peak. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - KZN Premier Sihle Zikalala says the province is facing the eye of the storm. The premier says over 16,000 beds have been reserved for COVID-19 patients. "We are now facing the storm, it is here with us. We are ready and prepared. "Right now we have 16,000 beds that will be assisting those who will be infected as the numbers continue to escalate," he said. READ: Over 300 workers at KZN hospital test positive for COVID-19 The premier is urging those infected to admit themselves for isolation in government facilities. "We are encouraging people to come forward once they have tested positive, let them come for self-isolation in government facilities as that will help us to monitor them." Zikalala was responding to the health minister's concern over the rising number of COVID-19 cases in the province. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.